    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have set `swapfile` and `directory` to save swapfiles into separated directory.\r\n\r\nIt works fine, but saving files into SSHFS mounted directory, NeoVim creates swap file where the original file exists. (like `._%`)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Mount SSHFS\r\n   ```bash\r\n   sshfs myserver:/some/directory ./mnt\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n2. Edit files in mounted directory with NeoVim\r\n3. List files\r\n   ```bash\r\n   ls -al\r\n   ```\r\n   ```\r\n   asdf@asdarf ~/project/mnt $ ls -al\r\n   total 80\r\n   drwxr-xr-x@ 1 asdf  staff   4096 Oct 18 12:55 .\r\n   drwxr-xr-x  9 asdf  staff    288 Oct 18 11:21 ..\r\n   -rw-r--r--  1 asdf  staff   4096 Oct 18 12:55 ._index.ts\r\n   -rw-r--r--  1 asdf  staff     39 Sep 27 20:09 .cs_files\r\n   drwxr-xr-x  1 asdf  staff   4096 Oct 18 11:25 .git\r\n   -rw-r--r--  1 asdf  staff     36 Sep 27 20:09 foo.js\r\n   -rw-r--r--  1 asdf  staff    147 Sep 27 20:09 index.js\r\n   -rw-r--r--@ 1 asdf  staff     68 Oct 18 12:55 index.ts\r\n   -rw-r--r--  1 asdf  staff  12288 Sep 22 17:25 tsconfig.json\r\n   ```\r\n   (See `._index.ts`)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSwapfile should not be listed as it is *not* supposed to be created at working directory.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 13.5 Ventura\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty 0.30.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew",
